# Component Standards

## Structure

- UI primitives live under `src/components/ui/` (e.g. `button/`, `link/`, `popup/`, `icon/`).
- Page sections live under `src/components/pages/<page>/`.
- Layout chrome lives under `src/components/layout/`.
- Components are presentational and stateless unless interactivity is required.
- Use typed Astro props with safe defaults; expose behavior via explicit props (`variant`, `lang`, etc.).
- One responsibility per component; prefer composition with `Container`, `Flex`, `Stack`.

## Links (required)

- Do **not** use raw `<a>` in pages or feature components.
- Use `Link.astro` for anchors (`variant`: `default`, `social`, `toolbar`, `card`, `unstyled`).
- Use `SocialLink.astro` for icon-only social links.
- Use `Button.astro` with `href` for CTA-style navigation (it wraps `Link` internally).
- Set `external={false}` for internal routes; omit or set `external` for `http(s)` / new-tab behavior.

## Icons

- SVGs live in `src/assets/icons/` (descriptive names: `close.svg`, `github.svg`).
- Render via `Icon.astro` (`name` matches filename without extension).

## Styles & scripts

- If a component has **more than 10 lines** of `<style>` or `<script>`, split into sibling files:
  - `ComponentName.styles.astro`
  - `ComponentName.scripts.astro`
- Import and render them at the bottom of the main component: `<ComponentNameStyles />`, `<ComponentNameScripts />`.
- Styles that target classes on **child** components (e.g. `Link`, `SocialLink`) must be **global**:
  - Prefer `src/styles/components.css` for shared patterns (toolbar, social links, modals), or
  - Use `<style is:global>` in the `.styles.astro` file.
- Do **not** rely on scoped styles in an empty `.styles.astro` wrapper for classes applied in other components.

## Accessibility

- Add `aria-label` / `aria-labelledby` on interactive and modal UI.
- Use semantic HTML (`nav`, `header`, `dialog`, `button` vs `div`).
